Notes:
------

 This data was measured as initial estimates
 and development of technique studying 
 load and line regulation characteristics.
 Particular sensitivity to the relationship
 of Load ground and grounds for control/adjust
 resistors of regulators for the load
 regulation.  Under 'optimal' conditions,
 measurements indicate load regulation of
 about 0.1-0.3%, consistent with data sheets.

 Line regulation is more difficult to
 measure and this data does not indicate
 better than a couple percent at maximum
 voltage and loading. 

 However, data-sheet consistent line regulation
 (~.3%) was obtained when output voltage is
 lowered away from dropout-sensitive values.
 I suspect that the poor line regulation at
 10 V output is due to drop-out and not
 regulation.

R=10 Ohms (nominal)
Connecting ground lead on oscilliscope caused
change of -0.06 V. (around 15:56 on Fri, Nov 3).

